1 packet Asian Greens
½ tin sweetcorn
1 packet beef strips
1 packet garlic paste
1 packet flat noodles
1 packet char siu paste
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
½ lime
1 packet Crispy Shallots
¼ cup water (for the sauce)
olive oil

• Roughly chop Asian greens.
Drain sweetcorn (1/2 tin for 2P /
1 tin for 4P)
• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over
medium-heat. Cook Asian greens
until just wilted, 2-3 mins. Transfer
to a bowl and set aside
• Return pan to high heat. Cook corn
until lightly browned, 4-5 mins
• Add beef, garlic paste and cook,
tossing, until browned, 1-2 mins

• Meanwhile, pierce a few holes in
noodle packet. Microwave until
steaming, 2 mins
• Slice lime into wedges

• Add char siu paste, sweet chilli,
water (1/4 cup for 2P / 1/2 cup for
4P), a squeeze of lime juice, greens
and noodles to the beef
• Toss to combine and divide
between plates
• Serve topped with crispy shallots